narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this class, with the caveat to make sure to check in on the first day of shopping week. Professor Zarin has a very idiomatic teaching style and I'm sure that she'd agree that it's not for everyone. That said, I took the class, worked hard on each essay, and loved it!

English 466 offers a good excuse to write â five essays of increasing length and an edited version of one at the end. I found the requirement to write to word counts quite restricting, but maybe you would like that. Professor Zarin's comments are pretty vague and she is pushy one-on-one, both conditions which I found to be frustrating. Other people seemed not to mind as much. Discussion is lively â expect to be cold called âÂ which is nice, and class feedback on students' essays was well-balanced.

An opportunity to learn from a thoughtful and talented writing professor. The class suffers sometimes from lack of structure, but there are many valuable opportunities to learn one-on-one with Prof Zarin.
